18/04/2011
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Ante Malic, vice-president of the Croatian Peasant Party-New Croatian Initiative (HSS-NHI), was shot dead late on Sunday (April 17th) at a restaurant in Tomislavgrad. The suspected killer is a police officer who is still on the run. The HSS-NHI says it is shocked by the killing and called for a thorough investigation. Police are searching for the perpetrator and refuse to speculate on a possible motive. (Fena, BHRT, Oslobodjenje, bh-news - 18/04/11)
